<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Buffer_overflow&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://iac.dtic.mil/iatac/download/Vol7_No4.pdf" class="external text" title="http://iac.dtic.mil/iatac/download/Vol7_No4.pdf" rel="nofollow">An Overview and Example of the Buffer-Overflow Exploit. pps. 16-21.</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.securecoding.cert.org" class="external text" title="https://www.securecoding.cert.org" rel="nofollow">CERT Secure Coding Standards</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cert.org/secure-coding" class="external text" title="http://www.cert.org/secure-coding" rel="nofollow">CERT Secure Coding Initiative</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cert.org/books/secure-coding" class="external text" title="http://www.cert.org/books/secure-coding" rel="nofollow">Secure Coding in C and C++</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.sans.org/reading_room/whitepapers/securecode/386.php" class="external text" title="http://www.sans.org/reading_room/whitepapers/securecode/386.php" rel="nofollow">SANS: inside the buffer overflow attack</a></li>
<li><a href="http://doc.bughunter.net/buffer-overflow/smash-stack.html" class="external text" title="http://doc.bughunter.net/buffer-overflow/smash-stack.html" rel="nofollow">"Smashing the Stack for Fun and Profit"</a> by Aleph One</li>
<li><a href="http://www.awarenetwork.org/etc/alpha/?x=5" class="external text" title="http://www.awarenetwork.org/etc/alpha/?x=5" rel="nofollow">"Advances in adjacent memory overflows"</a> by Nomenumbra</li>
<li><a href="http://www.blackhat.com/presentations/bh-usa-04/bh-us-04-silberman/bh-us-04-silberman-paper.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.blackhat.com/presentations/bh-usa-04/bh-us-04-silberman/bh-us-04-silberman-paper.pdf" rel="nofollow">A Comparison of Buffer Overflow Prevention Implementations and Weaknesses</a></li>
<li><a href="http://doc.bughunter.net/buffer-overflow/" class="external text" title="http://doc.bughunter.net/buffer-overflow/" rel="nofollow">More Security Whitepapers about Buffer Overflows</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.syngress.com/book_catalog/327_SSPC/sample.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.syngress.com/book_catalog/327_SSPC/sample.pdf" rel="nofollow">Chapter 12: Writing Exploits III</a> from <i>Sockets, Shellcode, Porting &amp; Coding: Reverse Engineering Exploits and Tool Coding for Security Professionals</i> by James C. Foster (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1597490059" class="internal">ISBN 1-59749-005-9</a>). Detailed explanation of how to use Metasploit to develop a buffer overflow exploit from scratch.</li>
<li><a href="http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/history/ande72.pdf" class="external text" title="http://csrc.nist.gov/publications/history/ande72.pdf" rel="nofollow">Computer Security Technology Planning Study</a>, James P. Anderson, ESD-TR-73-51, ESD/AFSC, Hanscom AFB, Bedford, MA 01731 (Oct. 1972) [NTIS AD-758 206]</li>
</ul>


